---
title: Curried Farro & Chickpeas with Roasted Broccoli and Yogurt Drizzle
description: We love farro, a nutrient-rich ancient grain, for its satisfyingly chewy texture and nutty flavor. Here, the rice alternative is combined with an aromatic curry sauce to form the base of these saucy bowls. They’re then topped with crisp, simply roasted broccoli and chickpeas roasted with curry powder. A dollop of creamy, cooling yogurt balances out the warming spices. Beyond farro’s bite, it’s a good source of fiber with zero cholesterol and fewer calories per serving than white rice that’ll keep you full and satisfied. Farro is also considered a “functional food,” meaning it can potentially have a positive impact on health when consumed regularly. It’s low in both total fat and saturated fat. Versatile farro is delicious in pretty much any dish, but we especially love it in soups, salads, and grain bowls.
